@startuml DEVELOPMENT_PROCESS

title **Human Operator Journey v2**\n(Stories-first Development Lifecycle)\nContinuation of IDEATION_PROCESS.puml

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333333
skinparam ActivityFontColor #111111
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9D6
skinparam NoteBorderColor #333333
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #999999
skinparam PartitionFontSize 14
skinparam DiamondBorderColor #333333
skinparam DiamondBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam DiamondFontSize 11

floating note left
  **Human Operator Journey**
  (Post-Ideation Development)
  ====
  **Prerequisite:**
  ""IDEATION_PROCESS.puml""
  completed (Gate G0 passed).
  ----
  **Truth Sources:**
  ""product/PRD.md"" = scope
  ""product/ARCH.md"" = arch
  ""product/contracts/*"" = APIs
  ""process/PROGRESS.md"" = state
  ----
  **Color Key:**
  <back:#D9ECFF>  Human action  </back>
  <back:#DFF7E1>  Agent activity  </back>
  <back:#FFF9D6>  Artifact output  </back>
  <back:#FFFDE7>  Decision gate  </back>
  <back:#FFF2CC>  Phase gate  </back>
  <back:#FFCDD2>  Escalation  </back>
  ----
  **All Workflows:**
  /seed /plan /explore /advise
  /next /check /ccr /release
  /archive /help
end note

start

:**Gate G0 -- Installed**
(from IDEATION_PROCESS.puml)
----
Artifacts committed to repo.
""make check"" runs green.
Agent activated as Process Steward.
PROGRESS.md initialized at P0.
----
Continues: Phase A (P1-P4); <<#FFF2CC>>

' =============================================
' PHASE A: COLLABORATIVE DESIGN (P1-P4)
' =============================================

partition "**PHASE A: COLLABORATIVE DESIGN** (P1-P4)\nARCH and contracts are DRAFTS -- freely modifiable" #E8F4FD {

  :**P1: Scope Framing** -- /plan
  ----
  **Human:** Type ""/plan"" in IDE chat.
  Provide your vision in PRD.md if not
  yet written. State priorities, MVP
  boundaries, and hard constraints.
  ----
  **Agent:** Reads PRD.md vision section.
  Drafts story backlog (S-V### entries)
  with acceptance criteria, risk tags
  (LOW/MED/HIGH), Given/When/Then format.
  Proposes functional grouping via UC tags
  (UC:SEARCH, UC:INGEST, UC:AUTH).
  Updates PROGRESS.md phase to P1.
  ----
  -> product/PRD.md S4 (stories); <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **Stories-first Principle**
    Stories are the boundary between
    human intent and agent execution.
    Each S-V### is a vertical slice
    deliverable in <= 1 day.
    **INVEST** criteria apply.
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md S4** Backlog
    + **PROGRESS.md** phase = P1
  end note

  if (Unknowns in domain,\ntech, or design?) then (yes)

    fork

      :**P1.a: Research Spike** -- /explore
      ----
      **Human:** Type ""/explore"" followed
      by your question. Examples:
      "Explore how cursor pagination works
      with our schema" or "Investigate
      available auth libraries for FastAPI."
      ----
      **Agent:** Performs read-only research.
      Reads source code, docs, and external
      references. Summarizes findings with
      evidence (code snippets, command output).
      Logs actionable findings as Issue (I-###)
      in PROGRESS.md. **No production code is
      changed. No decisions are recorded.**
      Feeds findings back to /plan scope.
      ----
      -> Findings summary in chat; <<#DFF7E1>>

      note left
        **Pure Investigation**
        /explore is a safe sandbox:
        no code changes, no logged
        decisions. Use for spikes,
        debugging, code audits,
        "how does X work?" questions.
        ----
        Output: Chat summary
        + optional **I-###** in PROGRESS
        Feeds back to **/plan**
      end note

    fork again

      :**P1.b: Decision Analysis** -- /advise
      ----
      **Human:** Type ""/advise"" followed by
      the decision context. Examples:
      "Advise: SQLite vs PostgreSQL for MVP"
      or "Advise: monolith vs microservices."
      ----
      **Agent:** Presents **2-3 options** with:
      tradeoffs (complexity, cost, risk),
      alignment with ARCH and PRD scope,
      scalability and maintenance impact.
      Gives explicit **recommendation** with
      rationale. Asks human to choose.
      After choice: **logs Decision (D-###)**
      in PROGRESS.md with rationale.
      May update ARCH.md or contracts
      if the decision reshapes them.
      ----
      -> D-### in PROGRESS.md; <<#D9ECFF>>

      note right
        **Structured Alternatives**
        Unlike /explore (research only),
        /advise always produces a
        **logged Decision (D-###)**.
        Each option shows tradeoffs.
        Human makes the final call.
        ----
        Output: **PROGRESS.md** D-###
        + may update ARCH/contracts
        (drafts in P0-P4, no CCR needed)
      end note

    end fork

  else (no)
  endif

  :**P2-P3: Architecture & Contracts** -- /plan
  ----
  **Human:** Review the agent's ARCH.md
  draft and contracts baseline. Focus on
  tech stack, conventions, boundaries, and
  extension points. Use /advise for any
  unresolved architectural tradeoffs.
  ----
  **Agent:** Drafts product/ARCH.md (repo
  map, naming conventions, C4-lite diagram,
  tech stack, security notes). Proposes
  minimal contracts baseline (schemas.py
  Pydantic models + openapi.yaml endpoints).
  Runs ""make check"" to validate contracts
  compile and tests pass. Updates PROGRESS.md
  phase to P2-P3. Logs significant changes
  as Decisions (D-###).
  ----
  -> product/ARCH.md + contracts/*; <<#DFF7E1>>

  note right
    **Draft Phase Freedom**
    ARCH and contracts are freely
    editable during P0-P4. No CCR
    required. Iterate as needed.
    Once approved at P4, they
    become **frozen** for build.
    ----
    Output: **ARCH.md S1-7**
    + **contracts/** baseline
    + **PROGRESS.md** D-### logged
  end note

  if (Architecture aligns\nwith vision and\nstories?) then (no)
    :Iterate: use /explore to
    research gaps, /advise for
    tradeoff decisions. Agent
    revises ARCH and contracts.
    Repeat until aligned.;
    note left
      **Design Feedback Loop**
      Iteration between /plan,
      /explore, and /advise is
      expected and encouraged.
      No ceremony required for
      draft-phase changes.
    end note
    -[#FF6600,dashed]->
  else (yes)
  endif

  :**P4: Baseline Approval** -- /plan
  ----
  **Human:** Open product/PRD.md and
  product/ARCH.md in your editor.
  Read every story (S-V###), its
  acceptance criteria, and the
  architecture rules. When satisfied,
  type **"Approved"** in IDE chat.
  This is the point of no return --
  ARCH and contracts lock to read-only.
  ----
  **Agent:** Finalizes story sequence and
  risk tags. Sets governance policy in
  PROGRESS.md (approval levels, CCR rules).
  Runs final ""make check"" to confirm
  ready-to-build state. Records gates
  G1 (scope approved) and G2 (ready-to-
  build) in PROGRESS.md with evidence.
  ----
  -> Approved PRD + locked ARCH; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **Governance Lockdown**
    After approval, ARCH.md and
    product/contracts/* become
    **read-only** during P5-P7.
    Any changes require a CCR
    (Contract Change Request)
    with human approval.
    ----
    Output: **PROGRESS.md** policy
    + G1 + G2 evidence
  end note

  :Artifacts: **PRD.md** (approved stories)
  + **ARCH.md** (locked architecture)
  + **contracts/** (locked interfaces)
  + **PROGRESS.md** (trackers initialized); <<#FFF9D6>>

  :**Gate G1 -- Scope Approved**
  (PRD stories accepted by Human)
  ----
  **Gate G2 -- Ready-to-Build**
  (contracts validate + check green); <<#FFF2CC>>

}

' =============================================
' PHASE B: DISCIPLINED BUILD (P5-P7)
' =============================================

partition "**PHASE B: DISCIPLINED BUILD** (P5-P7)\nARCH and contracts FROZEN -- changes require CCR" #F0F7E6 {

  repeat

    :**P5: JIT Task Planning** -- /next
    ----
    **Human:** Type ""/next"" in IDE chat.
    No additional context needed -- the
    agent tracks state via PROGRESS.md.
    ----
    **Agent:** Reads PRD story sequence and
    PROGRESS state. Selects next unstarted
    story (S-V###). Decomposes it into a
    JIT task checklist (5-15 atomic tasks
    T-V###.## with dependencies and risk
    tags). Marks story IN_PROGRESS. Updates
    PROGRESS.md phase to P5. Presents task
    plan for review.
    ----
    -> PROGRESS.md JIT task list; <<#DFF7E1>>

    note right
      **Just-In-Time Planning**
      Tasks are planned per-story,
      not upfront. The agent creates
      minimal atomic tasks right
      before execution. Each task
      maps to the parent story ID.
      ----
      Naming: **T-V###.##**
      (e.g., T-V001.01, T-V001.02)
      Output: **PROGRESS.md** tasks
    end note

    if (HIGH-risk\ntasks in plan?) then (yes)

      :**Human Risk Review**
      ----
      **Human:** Read the HIGH-risk tasks
      in PROGRESS.md. These involve
      destructive operations (DB drops,
      deploy scripts) or irreversible
      changes. Approve, reject, or
      modify each HIGH task.
      Type **"Approve"** per task.
      ----
      Agent STOPS on HIGH tasks
      until explicit approval.; <<#D9ECFF>>

    else (no)
      :Agent proceeds autonomously
      with LOW/MED tasks per policy.; <<#DFF7E1>>
    endif

    :**P6: Iterative Implementation** -- /next + /check
    ----
    **Human:** Keep typing ""/next"" to
    advance through each task. The agent
    handles one task per /next invocation.
    Remove hands from keyboard while the
    agent works. Monitor terminal output.
    ----
    **Agent:** For each task (T-V###.##):
    implements minimal code + unit tests,
    runs ""make check"" automatically,
    appends evidence to PROGRESS.md,
    marks task DONE if checks pass.
    Repeats until all story tasks complete.
    Updates PROGRESS.md phase to P6.
    ----
    -> app/ code + tests/; <<#DFF7E1>>

    note left
      **Minimal Implementation**
      Agent writes only enough code
      to satisfy each task. Tests run
      automatically via ""make check""
      after every change. Evidence
      logged per task.
      ----
      Output: Code + tests
      + **PROGRESS.md** evidence
      per task
    end note

    if (Agent detects\ncontract drift?) then (yes)

      :**P6.a: Contract Escalation** -- /ccr
      ----
      **Human:** The agent has **STOPPED**.
      Open PROGRESS.md and read CCR-###.
      It contains: failing evidence, what
      contract/ARCH rule is violated, a
      minimal change proposal, and impact
      analysis. You must respond with
      exactly one of:
      - **"APPROVE CCR-###"** -> apply change
      - **"REJECT CCR-###"** -> revert, recode
      - **"DEFER CCR-###"** -> block task, skip
      ----
      **Agent:** Detected mismatch between
      implementation reality and frozen
      contracts/ARCH. Created CCR-### entry.
      Marked current task BLOCKED. Cannot
      proceed or work around the mismatch
      until human decides.
      ----
      -> PROGRESS.md CCR-### entry; <<#FFCDD2>>

      note right
        **No Silent Workarounds**
        During P5-P7, the agent CANNOT
        modify contracts or ARCH. It
        must STOP and raise a CCR.
        This is the core safety gate
        preventing specification drift.
        ----
        APPROVE -> contracts updated,
        task resumes, ""make check"" re-run
        REJECT -> code reverted to honor
        original contract
        DEFER -> task stays BLOCKED,
        agent moves to next task
      end note

    else (no)
    endif

    if (Context window\nslowing down?) then (yes)

      :**P6.b: Context Cleanup** -- /archive
      ----
      **Human:** If the agent's responses
      degrade or it forgets constraints,
      type ""/archive"" to sweep completed
      logs from PROGRESS.md.
      ----
      **Agent:** Moves to archive file
      (process/archive/WIP-YYYYMMDD.md):
      completed tasks, closed CCRs,
      resolved Issues, old evidence.
      Keeps all active stories and tasks.
      Source code is never touched.
      ----
      -> process/archive/WIP-*.md; <<#DFF7E1>>

      note left
        **Context Maintenance**
        /archive only moves operational
        metadata. Active work and source
        code are untouched. Restores
        fast inference performance.
        ----
        Output: Lean PROGRESS.md
        + archive file registered
      end note

    else (no)
    endif

    :**P7: Story Acceptance** -- /next
    ----
    **Human:** Agent presents the completed
    story for acceptance. Boot the app
    (""make run"") and physically test the
    feature. Cross-reference results against
    acceptance criteria in PRD.md.
    Respond with:
    - **"PASS"** -> story is Done
    - **"FAIL + notes"** -> agent patches
      (e.g., "FAIL. Pagination returns
      wrong cursor after last page.")
    ----
    **Agent:** Summarizes what was built,
    tests passing, and acceptance criteria
    coverage. If FAIL: applies targeted
    fixes, re-runs ""make check"", asks
    for re-validation. If PASS: marks
    story DONE, records G3 evidence in
    PROGRESS.md, advances to next story.
    ----
    -> PROGRESS.md story status; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note right
      **Physical Validation**
      A green ""make check"" does NOT
      mean the feature works for humans.
      You MUST interact with the app
      or API output before approving.
      ----
      Output: **PROGRESS.md**
      S-V### = Done + G3 evidence
    end note

    :**Gate G3 -- Story Delivered**
    (acceptance met + check green)
    Repeats for each story in backlog.; <<#FFF2CC>>

  repeat while (More stories\nin PRD backlog?) is (yes) not (no)

  :Artifacts: All stories DONE
  Code + tests implemented
  Evidence logged per story
  PROGRESS.md fully tracked; <<#FFF9D6>>

}

' =============================================
' PHASE C: RELEASE & NEXT VERSION (P8-P12)
' =============================================

partition "**PHASE C: RELEASE & ITERATE** (P8-P12)" #FFF8E8 {

  :**P8-P10: Release Hardening** -- /release
  ----
  **Human:** Type ""/release"" in IDE chat.
  All PRD stories must be Done first.
  ----
  **Agent:** Updates PROGRESS.md phase to
  P8. Runs global integration checks and
  E2E tests (cross-story, not per-task).
  Fixes regressions found during global
  sweep. Drafts release notes + known
  issues + deployment runbook in PROGRESS.
  Optionally asks for manual E2E sign-off
  at P10 (smoke tests you run yourself).
  Records G4 evidence in PROGRESS.md.
  ----
  -> PROGRESS.md release notes; <<#DFF7E1>>

  note right
    **Global Verification**
    Unlike /check (per-task gate),
    /release runs cross-story
    integration and full E2E suite.
    Catches issues that isolated
    per-story testing missed.
    ----
    Output: **PROGRESS.md** release
    notes + G4 evidence
  end note

  :**Gate G4 -- Release Candidate**
  (hardening complete + E2E green); <<#FFF2CC>>

  :**P11: Deployment** -- /release
  ----
  **Human:** Deploy to staging/production
  using your preferred platform (Vercel,
  Fly.io, AWS, etc.). Follow the agent's
  deploy runbook. Run smoke tests against
  the live environment. Report back:
  **"DEPLOYED_OK"** or **"FAIL + logs."**
  ----
  **Agent:** Provides deployment checklist
  and expected verification steps. If FAIL:
  diagnoses from logs provided, proposes
  targeted fixes, re-runs ""make check"".
  If OK: records G5 in PROGRESS.md with
  deployment evidence and smoke results.
  ----
  -> Live deployment; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note left
    **Human-Controlled Deploy**
    The agent drafts the runbook
    but YOU physically deploy.
    The agent cannot push to prod
    autonomously. Deployment is
    always a human action.
    ----
    Output: **PROGRESS.md** G5
    + deployment confirmation
  end note

  if (Deploy\nsucceeded?) then (no)
    :Report failure to agent.
    Agent diagnoses from logs,
    fixes code, re-runs checks.
    Re-run /release -> re-deploy.;
    -[#FF6600,dashed]->
  else (yes)
  endif

  :**Gate G5 -- Released**
  (deployed + smoke OK + notes filed); <<#FFF2CC>>

  :**P12: Retrospective** -- /explore
  ----
  **Human:** Share feedback, telemetry
  summaries, user complaints, and next
  priorities. Use /explore to analyze
  what worked and what didn't. Use
  /advise for strategic next-version
  decisions.
  ----
  **Agent:** Summarizes version learnings.
  Proposes backlog candidates for next
  version. Updates PRD.md roadmap section
  with future story candidates. Logs
  retrospective findings in PROGRESS.md.
  ----
  -> PRD.md roadmap + learnings; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **Iteration Seed**
    Learnings from this version
    feed directly into the next
    version's planning cycle.
    Use /explore for analysis,
    /advise for strategic choices.
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md** roadmap
    + **PROGRESS.md** learnings
  end note

  :**P12.a: Version Archive** -- /archive
  ----
  **Human:** Type ""/archive"" to close out
  the completed version's tracking data.
  ----
  **Agent:** Moves all shipped stories,
  closed CCRs, resolved Issues, evidence,
  and release notes to archive file
  (process/archive/R-YYYYMMDD.md).
  Resets PROGRESS.md trackers for next
  version. Archive file becomes a
  read-only historical record.
  ----
  -> process/archive/R-*.md; <<#DFF7E1>>

  note left
    **Clean Slate**
    Archive preserves full history.
    PROGRESS.md resets with fresh
    trackers, ready for the next
    version's lifecycle.
    ----
    Output: Archive file
    + clean PROGRESS.md
  end note

  :Artifacts: Release notes archived
  PROGRESS.md reset for next version
  PRD.md roadmap updated with
  new story candidates; <<#FFF9D6>>
}

' =============================================
' VERSION LOOP
' =============================================

partition "**VERSION LOOP** (MVP -> V1.1 -> V2 ...)" #F5F0FF {

  if (Next version\nplanned?) then (yes)

    :Add new stories to PRD.md
    (tag for new version in roadmap).
    Update PROGRESS.md version label
    and reset gate statuses (G0-G5).
    ----
    **Return to Phase A (P1-P4).**
    Run /plan to scope new version.
    Use /explore and /advise for
    new architectural decisions.
    ARCH/contracts unlock as drafts.
    ----
    Development lifecycle repeats.; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note right
      **Continuous Delivery**
      Each version follows the same
      Phase A -> B -> C progression
      with G0-G5 gate milestones.
      Lessons from P12 retrospective
      inform the next version's scope.
      ----
      **Version Naming:**
      Stories: S-V### (V = version)
      Tasks: T-V###.## (per story)
    end note

  else (no)

    :Project complete.
    All planned versions delivered.
    Archive contains full history.; <<#FFF9D6>>

  endif
}

stop

@enduml
